The '''Association for the History of Chiropractic''', founded in 1980, promotes the [[Scholarly method|scholarly]] study and recording of the history of [[chiropractic]]. It publishes books and the [[Academic journal|journal]] ''Chiropractic History'', holds an annual meeting, and gives an annual award. Membership is open to anyone with an interest.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://historyofchiropractic.org/mc/page.do |title= Association for the History of Chiropractic |accessdate=2008-07-08| archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20080606170921/http://www.historyofchiropractic.org/mc/page.do| archivedate= 6 June 2008 <!--DASHBot-->| deadurl= no}}</ref>

