{{Infobox company | name = Bosnalijek | logo = Bosnalijek logo.png | type = [[public company|Public]] ([[Sarajevo Stock Exchange|SASE]]: [https://web.archive.org/web/20080926154021/http://www.sase.ba/DesktopDefault.aspx?tabid=26&symbol=BSNLR BSNLR]) | foundation = 1951 | location = [[Sarajevo]], [[Bosnia and Herzegovina]] | key_people = Nedim Uzunović <small>([[Director-general|Chief Executive Officer]])</small> | industry = Pharmaceutical | products = Solid oral form medicines, ampule medicines, galenic products, non-pharmaceutical chemical products | revenue = {{increase}} 153 [[million]] [[Convertible mark|BAM]] (2017) | net_income = 13 [[million]] [[Convertible mark|BAM]] (2017) | num_employees = 845 (2018) | homepage = http://www.bosnalijek.com/ }}
'''Bosnalijek''' is the largest [[pharmaceutical company]] in [[Bosnia and Herzegovina]]. The organisation was established in 1951 and employs ~620 workers, out of which more than 50% have university level or higher qualifications. Its product portfolio consists of ~180 products. The company continues investment into R&D. Bosnalijek has established collaboration with several world-leading companies from the industry.<ref>[http://www.bosnalijek.ba/eng/default.wbsp?p=82 Short overview of Bosnalijek]</ref>
Bosnalijek is present in 22 countries worldwide: all neighbouring southeastern European countries, most eastern European countries, [[Libya]] and many French-speaking African countries, several countries from the [[Arabian peninsula]] and [[Caucasus]], etc.<ref>[http://www.bosnalijek.ba/eng/default.wbsp?p=91 Bosnalijek worldwide]</ref>
In 2005, [[International Finance Corporation]] provided Bosnalijek with a [[Euro|€]]7.5 million loan for the construction of an €18.5 million production and distribution center.<ref>[http://ifcln001.worldbank.org/ifcext/eca.nsf/Content/SelectedProjectBosnia?OpenDocument&UNID=0B9E73628312552185256FB300801FC1 Summary of Project Information, Project Number 24017]{{dead link|date=November 2016 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}, International Finance Corporation, World Bank Group. Accessed 2008-01-14.</ref>
